# Claude Code — Global Instructions

## Language & Communication
- Communicate in {{LANGUAGE}}, code and variables in English
- Result first, no filler
- User decides scope — AI writes all code

## Identity
- Name: {{USER_NAME}}, Email: {{USER_EMAIL}}
- Commits must only use the configured user identity — no additional attribution

## Quality Standards
- WCAG AA, OWASP Top 10, SEO basics
- DSGVO-compliant (self-hosted fonts, no external tracking)
- No hardcoded versions — always check live (context7, npm view, WebSearch)

## Deployment
- Default target: {{DEPLOYMENT_TARGET}}

## Git & CI/CD
- Conventional Commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, refactor:)
- No auto-push, always `git status` + `git diff` before commit
- Run tests before commit when available
- After push: `gh run list --limit 1` — fix failures immediately

## Error Handling (CRITICAL)
- On error: stop, explain, suggest alternative. 3x same error → 2 alternatives
- Root cause analysis REQUIRED: SYMPTOM → CONTEXT → CAUSE → FIX → PREVENTION

## Code Standards
- Read before modifying, respect existing patterns
- Working code: ASK before changing
- Quality over speed, consider downstream effects

## Cleanup (CRITICAL)
Leave workspace cleaner than you found it. Always clean up temp files.
Session end: `git status`, delete temp files

## Deviation Handling
Auto-fix: Bug/typo, dep patch/minor. Ask user: Major, architecture, new tool.
Security CRITICAL: Fix + inform. When in doubt, ask.

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- Scope explosion, phantom fix, cargo cult config, silent failure
- Verify: IDENTIFY → RUN → READ → VERIFY → CLAIM
- No stub blindness, context amnesia, over-engineering, littering

## Skills & Plugins
- Before complex actions: check for matching skill in ~/.claude/skills/
- Prefer plugins when available
